CandMessageSchema.description: Schema describing what the Candidate Message should contain.

bbox.description: Shapely object representing a bounding box

cluster_set.description: Set of candidate cand_id's this candidate is in a cluster with, should always include at least it's own cand_id.

diameter.description: Estimate of the diameter of the object in mm

find_info_dict.description: Dictionary of different find position and associated information

basic.description: Information about a specific find position and observation

feature_pos.description: The global position of a point of visible flesh on the candidate

feature_pos_rel.description: The point of visible flesh on the candidate in relation to the gpos

find_pos.description: x,y,z,r global position of the schnoz when the camera had the best view

find_score.description: score value returned from tracker about the candidates current find ray.

obs_match_conf.description: 0 to 1 confidence of the match from the find ray obs.

obs_match_type.description: 0 for bbox matched obs 1 for template matched

obs_occlusion.description: Classification of the occlusion of the berry for the current find ray obs. Bdetector_iface has more explanation for these classifications

obs_pos_error.description: error between the position from the obs and the position from MHT

pick_pos.description: x,y,z,r global position of the camera when it had its best view of the berry.

x_zen.description: -1 to 1 value describing where the relation of the find ray to the berry, 1 is directly above -1 if directly below.

y_zen.description: -1 to 1 value describing where the relation of the find ray to the berry, 1 is directly above -1 if directly below.

obs_match_type.description: 0 for bbox matched obs 1 for template matched

y_zen.description: -1 to 1 value describing where the relation of the find ray to the berry, 1 is directly above -1 if directly below.

general_occlusion.description: Classification of the occlusion of the berry for all views. Bdetector_iface has more explanation for these classifications

obs_ids.description: List of all obs ids that were associated together to create this candidate.

observed.description: Representation of if the candidate was observed in the last observation

orientation.description: Classification of the orientation of the berry. Bdetector_iface has more explanation for these classifications

plant_id.description: Candidate ID of the plant this candidate is attached to.

plant_pos.description: Position of the plant this candidate is attached to.

ripeness.description: Percentage confidence that the candidate is ripe

score.description: Score metric from MultiHypothesesTracker, 0 represents lowest confidence while -inf represents the highest possible confidence

ObsMessageSchema.description: Schema describing what the Obs message should contain.

type.description: Message send from obscore every frame

mask.description: flag for if the camera is running the detector, if this flag is low there should not be any berry objects

match_dict.description: Dictionary of berry and plant matches that were found by the detector

items.description: dictionary of obs_type to pairs of matched observation

bbox.description: Shapely object representing a bounding box

cam_id.description: Camera that took the obs, 0 for left 1 for right

cam_pos.description: Location of the observed item with respect to the camera. Represented as an [x,y,z] distance in millimeters

det_conf.description: Confidence the model has that the observation is not a false positive

feature_point.description: x, y point in the image that matches a point on the other side of the frame

feature_pos.description: point in global space from triangulating between two obs feature points

frame_count.description: Number of frames since recording started

match_conf.description: Metric for how confident the system is that the match point is the same position on the berry in the left and right frame

num_pixels.description: Number of pixels that contain ripe berry flesh

occlusion.description: Classification of the occlusion of the berry. Bdetector_iface has more explications for these classifications

orientation.description: The classification of the orientation of the berry. Bdetector_iface has more explications for these classifications

ray.description: Ray from the camera to the observed item, the start of the ray is the origin and the end of the ray is a normalized point.

ray_angle.description: bounding angle of the bbox in the imagers frustum

ripeness.description: The percentage chance that this obs is ripe, from 0 to 1

triangulation_point.description: x, y point. The center of the berry, calculated through some matching algorithm
